The President and Ambassador Apartments are two five-story apartment buildings in Lincoln, Nebraska. They were built in 1928â€“1929 on land owned by Levi Leland Coryell, and designed in the Art Deco style by architect John A. Alexander. They belonged to the L. L. Coryell Building Corporation until 1979. They have been listed on the National Register of Historic Places since December 10, 1993.
